    "answer": "## Findings\n\n### Current Attachment UI\n- **File**: `src/VisualRelay.App/Views/Controls/TaskDetailPanel.axaml` (lines 215\u2013259)\n- Attachments are rendered in an **\"Attachments\" `TabItem`** via an `ItemsControl` bound to `{Binding Attachments}`.\n- Each attachment uses a **`DataTemplate` with `x:DataType=\"vm:AttachmentRowViewModel\"`** (compiled bindings enabled).\n- Current template shows a `DockPanel` with: **\"Remove\" button** (right), **\"Reveal\" button** (right), and a **`TextBlock`** showing the file path via `HomePathToTildeConverter`.\n- No image preview exists today.\n\n### AttachmentRowViewModel\n- **File**: `src/VisualRelay.App/ViewModels/AttachmentRowViewModel.cs`\n- Simple record-like class with three properties: `Path` (string), `RevealCommand` (IRelayCommand), `RemoveCommand` (IRelayCommand).\n- No `IsImage` flag, no image preview property, no open-image command.\n- Extends `ViewModelBase` (which is `ObservableObject` from CommunityToolkit.Mvvm).\n\n### Attachment Population\n- **File**: `src/VisualRelay.App/ViewModels/MainWindowViewModel.Helpers.cs` (lines 215\u2013228)\n- `RebuildAttachments()` clears and repopulates the `Attachments` collection from `task.SiblingPaths`.\n- Currently constructs `new AttachmentRowViewModel(path, revealCmd, removeCmd)` with simple `RelayCommand` wrappers.\n- Called from `OnSelectedTaskChanged()` in `MainWindowViewModel.Commands.cs`.\n\n### Task / Attachment Model\n- **File**: `src/VisualRelay.Domain/RelayTaskItem.cs` \u2014 `SiblingPaths` is `IReadOnlyList<string>` of full filesystem paths.\n- **File**: `src/VisualRelay.Core/Tasks/RelayTaskRepository.cs` \u2014 `EmitSingleTaskFromFolder()` collects all non-`.md` files in a task directory as siblings (attachments).\n\n### Image Handling Primitives\n- **Avalonia 12.0.5** \u2014 `Avalonia.Media.Imaging.Bitmap` can load from a file path: `new Bitmap(filePath)`. The `Image` control's `Source` property accepts `IImage` (which `Bitmap` implements).\n- **No existing image-loading pattern** in the codebase; no `Image` elements anywhere in XAML.\n- **`TopLevel.Launcher`** is available for opening files via the OS default handler: `TopLevel.GetTopLevel(this)?.Launcher.LaunchFileInfoAsync(new FileInfo(path))`. Used in `TopBar.axaml.cs`, `StageInputView.axaml.cs`, `StageOutputView.axaml.cs`.\n\n### Converter Patterns\n- Converters live in `src/VisualRelay.App/Views/Controls/` and follow a **singleton-with-`Instance`** pattern (see `HomePathToTildeConverter.cs`, `BoolNotConverter.cs`).\n- Built-in converters (`ObjectConverters.IsNotNull`, `StringConverters.IsNotNullOrEmpty`, `BoolConverters.Not`) are used throughout.\n\n### Project Configuration\n- **Compiled bindings enabled** (`AvaloniaUseCompiledBindingsByDefault=true`) \u2014 DataTemplates with `x:DataType` enforce type-safe bindings.\n- **No `DataTemplateSelector`** exists in the codebase \u2014 would need creation if choosing Option B.\n- **No `Image` references** in any `.axaml` file currently.\n\n---\n\n## Constraints\n1. **Preserve existing buttons** \u2014 The \"Reveal\" and \"Remove\" buttons must remain visible for image attachments (the task explicitly states this).\n2. **Image sizing: 50\u201375% of panel width** \u2014 Images must be displayed large enough to be somewhat readable. This requires either a parent-width-relative `MaxWidth` binding (~0.75) or a fixed `MaxWidth` large enough to fit within the ~300\u2013400px panel.\n3. **Click opens image in default viewer** \u2014 Clicking the image must invoke the OS default handler (same effect as \"Reveal\" but opening the image file). Use `TopLevel.Launcher.LaunchFileInfoAsync()`.\n4. **Compiled bindings** \u2014 The existing `DataTemplate` uses `x:DataType=\"vm:AttachmentRowViewModel\"`, so any new bindings must be compatible with compiled bindings or use converters.\n5. **Minimal new files preferred** \u2014 The Ideate stage recommended Option A (lowest-touch: add `Image` element + converter + code-behind handler), which requires one new converter file plus modifications to existing files.\n6. **No async loading infrastructure** \u2014 There is no existing lazy/async image loading pattern; initial implementation should use synchronous `Bitmap` loading (acceptable for typical screenshot-sized attachments). A follow-up could add deferred loading if performance is an issue.\n7. **File extension detection** \u2014 Known image extensions to support: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.gif`, `.bmp`, `.webp` (standard web/image formats). Detection can happen via converter (Option A) or ViewModel property (Option C).\n8. **Theme consistency** \u2014 The dark theme (`#12151B` panel background) must be considered when rendering images. No additional styling beyond sizing should be needed.\n\n```json\n{ \"findings\": \"The attachment UI lives in TaskDetailPanel.axaml (Attachments tab) using an ItemsControl with a DataTemplate over AttachmentRowViewModel (Path, RevealCommand, RemoveCommand). Attachments are populated from task SiblingPaths (full filesystem paths). No image preview, image detection, or click-to-open functionality exists today. Avalonia 12.0.5 provides Bitmap (from Avalonia.Media.Imaging) for file loading and TopLevel.Launcher.LaunchFileInfoAsync() for OS-default file opening. Converters follow a singleton-Instance pattern in Views/Controls/. Compiled bindings are enabled project-wide. No DataTemplateSelector or Image elements exist in the codebase currently.\", \"constraints\": [\"Preserve existing Reveal and Remove buttons for image attachments\", \"Image sizing must be 50\u201375% of available panel width (use ~0.75 * parent ActualWidth via converter or MaxWidth)\", \"Clicking the image must open it in the default OS viewer via TopLevel.Launcher.LaunchFileInfoAsync()\", \"Compiled bindings (x:DataType) are active in the DataTemplate \u2014 new bindings must work with them\", \"Minimal file changes preferred (Option A: one new converter + XAML/code-behind edits)\", \"No existing async image loading \u2014 synchronous Bitmap(filePath) is acceptable for initial implementation\", \"Supported image extensions: .png, .jpg, .jpeg, .gif, .bmp, .webp\", \"Dark theme background (#12151B) must be considered for image rendering\"] }\n```",
